  "prompt": "Why does Peter Thiel hate Gawker?",
  "response": "Peter Thiel's animosity towards Gawker Media largely stems from the publication's role in revealing his sexual orientation in a 2007 article, which he felt was a violation of his privacy and dignity. He viewed Gawker as a publication that engaged in what he considered to be unethical journalism, often focusing on sensationalism and personal attacks. This personal grievance led to Thiel financing a legal battle against Gawker, which eventually contributed to the company's bankruptcy in 2016 after a high-profile lawsuit brought by Hulk Hogan, whom Thiel secretly supported. Thiel's actions were seen as a broader statement against media practices that he deemed harmful, but they also ignited discussions about the power of wealth in influencing media narratives and legal outcomes.",
